The Florida State Fair opened on Thursday featuring fried foods, entertainment and plenty of farm animals to pet. Rides included “Street Fighter” the thrill seekers or the tried-and-true Ferris wheel for the risk-averse. From Feb. 10-21, visitors can purchase tickets to the fair, which has several discount days and even a Valentine date option. Read: Florida State Fair offers price breaks on promotion days in Tampa In the meantime, plan your day by diving into this set of photos from opening day on Thursday.